to the editor your assertion editorial jan 7 that the nuclear regulatory commission was negligent for allowing a brief period of continued operation of the davis besse nuclear power plant in oak harbor ohio before inspections does not acknowledge the unanimous decision by the relevant expert staff that continued operation would not pose a significant safety risk assuring protection of the public health and safety is the nrc 's highest priority no one was aware of the reactor vessel head corrosion that was discovered in the subsequent inspections a safety judgment rather than costs to the licensee guided the nrc 's decision the nrc has been highly critical of both licensee and staff shortcomings in connection with the unexpected head corrosion and we are taking stern corrective measures to ensure no recurrences claims of nrc timidity are unjustified richard a meserve chairman nuclear regulatory commission rockville md jan 7 2003

